temp.fibHeap.stixar.graph.attr
Interface NativeNodeMatrix

All Superinterfaces:
NodeData
All Known Implementing Classes:
ByteNodeMatrix, CharNodeMatrix, DoubleNodeMatrix, FloatNodeMatrix, IntNodeMatrix, LongNodeMatrix
public interface NativeNodeMatrix
extends NodeData

Marker Interface for a set of node attributes stored and accessed via arrays of native types.

NativeNodeMaps provide a much more efficient mechanism for storing numeric attributes than via the use of generics. The reason for this is that with generics, algorithms with numeric requirements, such as shortests paths, end up boxing and unboxing numbers all the time. Where speed is important, NativeNodeMaps are the preferred attribute mechanism for numeric attributes.

Available native attribute types:
  • IntNodeMap
  • FloatNodeMap
  • LongNodeMap
  • DoubleNodeMap
  • CharNodeMap
  • ByteNodeMap
